The article is a speech given by President Joe Biden at the Boys & Girls Club of West San Gabriel Valley in Monterey Park, California. The speech addresses the recent mass shooting that took place in the Asian American community and pays tribute to the victims. President Biden expresses his condolences to the families affected by the tragedy and shares his own personal experience with loss. He also announces a new executive order aimed at implementing stricter background checks for firearm sales and holding the gun industry accountable. The President emphasizes the need for Congress to take further action, including banning assault weapons and high-capacity magazines. He concludes by offering words of comfort and hope to the grieving community.